<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aleksandrov Returns From Romania, Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2901180694 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 
GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2901180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A total agreement was reached on all issues that 
were discussed, Defense Minister Aleksandrov said upon his 
return from Romania, where he had talks with his counterpart, 
Nicolae Spiroiu. 
  Refraining by all means from interfering in the Yugoslav 
conflict and a total support of the Yugoembargo was the joint 
position of the two defense ministers. Regarding the war in 
former Yugoslavia, the opinion was expressed that diplomatic 
means to stop the war are far from being exhausted. 

</TEXT>

