<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Thousands Wait To Hear Speech </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101121394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1131 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3101121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bijeljina, 31 Jan (TANJUG) -- Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, 
chairman of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia, arrived in 
Bijeljina shortly before 1100. Outside the municipal assembly 
building he was welcomed by Radovan Karadzic, president of the 
Srpska republic, and by Prime Minister Vladimir Lukic. 
  Greetings were exchanged during a cordial meeting and on 
this 
occasion Zhirinovskiy told Karadzic that wherever he goes he 
finds "proofs and monuments indicating that the Serb nation is a 
historic nation." 
  The host and his guest then went to the municipal assembly 
building where talks are to be held. More than 10,000 people 
have been waiting at the city square in Bijeljina since early 
this morning to hear Zhirinovskiy and Karadzic speak. 

</TEXT>

