<H3> <TI>   Croatian Army Units Gather Near Gornji Vakuf </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3001152094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3001152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Seven brigades of the Croatian Army, assisted by 
paramilitary formations of the Croatian Defense Council [HVO], 
are continuing their fierce attacks in the direction of Gornji 
Vakuf and the river Lasva valley, the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army's 
press center has announced. 
  Fighters from Sibenik, Osijek, Vukovar, Vinkovci, Varazdin, 
and Zagreb are amassing around Gornji Vakuf with constant 
artillery support. Zagreb's assurances that these are not 
Croatian Army units, but volunteers from Bosnia were already 
heard at the beginning of the Serb aggression against the 
internationally recognized Bosnia-Herzegovina. [passage omitted] 

