<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hunger Claims `Dozens' in Free Doboj Territory </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2801154194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2801154194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mirudin Aldobasic] </F>
  [Text] Tesanj--There have been more victims of exhaustion 
and hunger on the free Teslic territories. This time it is the 
case of two older people, whom even the doctors unfortunately 
could not help. They died from starvation. Let me remind you: 
The last convoy with humanitarian aid that reached this region 
was exactly seven months ago. Starvation and exhaustion have 
also claimed dozens of lives on the free Doboj territories. 
Almost 20,000 elderly, women, and children are facing death. 
  The situation is particularly hard in Matuzici, Ularice, 
Alibegovci, Mravici, [word indistinct], Mala Brijesnica and 
Velika Brijesnica, Kokotnica, and other places on the free 
territory. Over the last seven months, only two kilograms of 
flour per household have been distributed here. 
  There is a real humanitarian catastrophe on the Maglaj 
territory, too. Tesanj, with 20,000 refugees from Doboj and 
Teslic, has also been for a long time been without food, 
electricity, fuel, and warm clothes. 

</TEXT>

