<H3> <TI>   Banka Luka ICRC Resumes Aid Deliveries </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3001132094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1212 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3001132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Banja Luka, 30 Jan (TANJUG) -- Humanitarian aid 
convoys organized by the Banja Luka delegation of the ICRC 
[International Committee of the Red Cross], which have been 
suspended since 17 January this year, will start running again 
today, a TANJUG correspondent has learned. 
  A convoy for the local population will arrive in [Serb-held] 
Banja Luka today, as well as another one destined for 
[Muslim-held] Zenica. Both have been inspected at the border 
crossing [between Croatia and Bosnia] in [former Bosanska] 
Gradiska on the river Sava. 
  As has been reported, the Banja Luka delegation of the ICRC 
temporarily suspended aid deliveries following the incident when 
an explosive device was planted under an ICRC vehicle [in Banja 
Luka] on 17 January this year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-50397 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu020_i_94014" </HT>


