<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Threatens To Punish `Enemies' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU3001201794 Podgorica TVCG Television Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1830 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU3001201794 </F>
<F P=104>  Podgorica TVCG Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Milenko Ilic] </F>
  [Text] [Studio announcer] Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, 
president of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia, today 
arrived in Subotica from Slovenia. He should be arriving in 
Belgrade this evening. 
  [Ilic] Currently the most controversial person on the 
international political scene, Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of 
the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia, arrived this afternoon 
in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia at the invitation of the 
Serbian Democratic Party of all Serbian Lands and the 
Serbian-Russian Friendship Society. He was welcomed at the 
Hungarian-Yugoslav border crossing by Radomir Smiljanic. 
Expressing thanks for the welcome, Zhirinovskiy said that he 
was happy that he had stepped onto Serbian soil, onto the 
beginning of the Slav world, and that he was among the people 
who are today fervently fighting for all the Slavs. 
  After a brief traditional Orthodox ceremony, Zhirinovskiy 
went to Subotica, where he was greeted by many citizens. 
Addressing them, he said: I am coming to your country for the 
first time, but I am coming here as a representative of the 
victorious party at the Russian elections, as a representative 
of Russia, which has chosen a new course. This course is the 
obligation of Russia to help the brotherly Serbian people. Our 
enemies are our common enemies and you ought to know that they 
will be punished for all the evils committed against the Slav 
people. 
  A new era is beginning, Zhirinovskiy said. His words were 
accompanied with chanting: Russia, Serbia. He stressed that the 
enemies of the Slav people are now trembling in Paris, Bonn, 
London, and Washington. 
  Commenting on the war the Serbian people are waging on the 
territory of the former Yugoslavia, Zhirinovskiy said that all 
the barbarians that have settled on the sacred Serbian soil must 
accept the fact that this land belongs to the Serbian people, or 
leave it. 
  After a brief stop in a big restaurant in Subotica, Agros 
Centar, Vladimir Zhirinovskiy continued his journey to Belgrade, 
where he will hold a news conference. According to the plan, 
Zhirinovskiy will visit Bijeljina as a guest of the republic of 
Srpska, and then meet Milan Martic, newly elected president of 
the republic of Serbian Krajina, in Vukovar. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

