<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Democratic Party President Micunovic Resigns </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2901200594 Belgrade RTB Television Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1830 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2901200594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade RTB Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The denouement of the dispute between Dragoljub 
Micunovic, president of the Democratic Party, and Zoran 
Djindjic, president of the party's Executive Committee, over the 
concept of how the Democratic Party should be led, is known. As 
we have learned, Dragoljub Micunovic, president of the 
Democratic Party, has tendered his resignation as president, 
which was greeted by a tumultuous applause. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

