<H3> <TI>   SDL Says Meciar Trying To Break Up Party </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2801172194 Bratislava SME in Slovak 26 Jan 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU2801172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava SME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "(dos)": "Weiss: The Party of the Democratic </F>
Left Is Next, After the Slovak National Party,"] 
  [Text] Bratislava--I know that the Party of the Democratic 
Left [SDL] is next, after the Slovak National Party [SNS], but 
the methods that were used to break up the SNS will not be 
successful with the SDL. This statement was made yesterday by 
SDL Chairman Peter Weiss. He described the claim made by Deputy 
Prime Minister S. Kozlik that P. Weiss and L. Pittner voted 
intentionally for the draft state budget as a deliberate 
political lie. "I know that the prime minister waited 
impatiently for the outcome of the SDL Executive Committee 
meeting and that he expected me to resign," said Weiss in this 
context. According to him, differences are beginning to crop up 
within the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia [HZDS] between 
those who want to continue democratically to fulfill the HZDS' 
preelection program and those who, despite their deputy's 
mandate, also have posts in the state administration and are 
interested in privatization. Weiss considers the visit to 
Slovakia by representatives from the Hungarian Democratic Forum 
[MDF] to be part of the preelection campaign organized by the 
party, which is trying to ward off the threat of electoral 
defeat. Weiss announced that L. Fogas (SDL), the leader of the 
group of National Council of the Slovak Republic deputies in the 
Council of Europe Parliamentary Assembly, has been elected one 
of its deputy chairmen. 

</TEXT>

