<H3> <TI>   Decision To Stop RFE Broadcasts Reversed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2801224294 Bratislava STV 1 Television Network in Slovak 
2130 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2801224294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava STV 1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Slovak Telecommunications [company] has reversed 
its decision to terminate its contract with Radio Free Europe 
[RFE] on 31 January 1994. The company will take steps toward 
solving technical and legal issues concerning RFE broadcasts via 
transmitters in the Slovak Republic. 
  According to a memorandum of understanding signed by RFE 
Deputy Director Gary Thatcher and Vladmir Ondrovic, director of 
Slovak Communications, in Bratislava today, the RFE is open to 
further negotiations. 

