<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Calls for Tolerance, Peace in New Year </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL3012182293 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1600 
GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> FL3012182293 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Armed Forces general command asks that the cycle 
of violence created by division be ended. Without naming the 
serious incidents at the beginning of the week in Cite Soleil, 
the military institution asks all sons of the country for more 
peace and tolerance and expresses hope that the coming year will 
be the beginning of a new era for all, auguring the 
establishment of a real democracy and a state of law 
guaranteeing more justice to all Haitians and better prospects 
for their children. 
  It should be noted that more than (5,000 million) gourdes 
have been collected within the framework of humanitarian 
assistance for the victims of Cite Soleil. Furthermore, the U.S. 
Government is studying the possibility of a long-term 
reaccommodation for those people. A protocol of assistance was 
signed on 29 December between the United States, the Haitian 
Government, and the health centers. 

</TEXT>

