<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports Through 30 Dec </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0101221594 </F>
<F P=103> PY0101221594 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Chile monitored through 30 
December. 
  The profits of the Copper Corporation's Chuquicamata 
Division 
will amount to $385 million this year, a drop of 43 percent 
compared with 1992. Production this year will total 615,000 
metric tons, which means that the company fulfilled its 
production plan by 102.3 percent. Investments were $207 million 
compared with 1992 when they were $206 million. (Santiago EL 
MERCURIO in Spanish 17 Dec 93 pp B1-B20) 
  The Institute for Export Promotion has reported that from 
January to October Chilean exports to Europe totaled $2.179 
billion and those to the Middle East totalled $70.8 million, a 
drop of 19 percent and 3.2 percent respectively compared with 
the same period last year. Exports to Latin America totaled 
$1.560 billion, an increase of 12 percent during the same 
period. (Santiago EL MERCURIO in Spanish 14 Dec 93 Economic and 
Business Section p B2) 

</TEXT>

