<H3> <TI>   Roberto Escobar Asks Los Pepes for Peace Following Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0301033494 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1800 GMT 2 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0301033494 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "NTC News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Roberto Escobar Gaviria, who is recovering from 
injuries sustained during an attack against him at the Itagui 
Maximum Security Prison, today issued from the military hospital 
a Peace Communique, which was written and signed by his mother, 
Hermelinda Gaviria de Escobar. In the communique, Escobar 
claims to be the spokesman for the Escobar family and the 
arrested members of the Medellin Cartel in various Colombian 
prisons and asks Los Pepes [Persecuted by Pablo Escobar] for 
peace. The brother of the former chief of the Medellin Cartel 
asks his archenemies to seek a negotiated and public solution to 
the conflicts they maintain with his group. 
  Roberto Escobar said his family has maintained a peaceful 
attitude despite the attacks they have sustained following the 
death of the Medellin Cartel capo. Roberto Escobar remains 
under medical surveillance at the military hospital after the 
Pepes attacked him at the Itagui Maximum Security Prison. It 
has been unofficially learned that there is little chance that 
the brother of late drug kingpin Pablo Escobar Gaviria will 
recover his vision following this attack. 

</TEXT>

