<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister: Colombian Relations `Excellent' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA3112033493 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 2350 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> PA3112033493 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Rayma Rondon; from "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Defense Minister Vice Admiral Radamez Munoz Leon 
gave assurances that relations between Venezuela and Colombia 
have never been better. He also assured that the relations 
between the Armed Forces of both countries are excellent and 
that the measures Colombia is taking to reinforce Venezuelan 
border surveillance are the best possible. 
  [Begin Munoz recording] Never have relations with Colombia 
been as good as they are now. The relationship between both 
Armed Forces go further than the personal friendship between the 
heads of the Colombian and Venezuelan Armed Forces and this also 
holds true for the defense ministers -- relations are excellent. 
I believe the measures Colombia is taking to support our 
domestic measures is a great demonstration of a broad support 
based on the various international agreements exercised through 
both defense ministers and the various military commanders, both 
Colombian and Venezuelan. The agreements we have are being 
honored. [end recording] 
  Likewise, the defense minister reported that starting 
January 
greater border security efficiency is to be expected. Regarding 
the possibility that civilian and military personnel in the 
Amparo Case [alleged border massacre] may be pardoned, Munoz 
said that the president is studying the case together with other 
cases. 

</TEXT>

