<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Rebel Group </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0101200694 Paris AFP in Spanish 1908 GMT 1 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0101200694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 1 Jan (AFP) -- According to several 
sources, a group of Indians rose up in arms today and seized by 
force the mayor's office in San Cristobal de las Casas in the 
southern state of Chiapas. 
  In a communique, the rebels announced the creation of a 
guerrilla group called the Zapata National Liberation Army 
[Ejercito Zapatista de Liberacion Nacional -- EZLN]. The 
communique calls on EZLN forces "to advance toward the capital 
of the country, defeat the Mexican Federal Army, protect the 
civilian population during this liberating advance, and allow 
the liberated people to elect their own administrative 
authorities in a free and democratic manner." 
  Eyewitness Ernesto Riedwyl told AFP that in San Cristobal de 
las Casas some 200-300 people took over the municipal palace. 
According to Riedwyl, these people are now engaged in 
destroying and looting the building. Riedwyl said: "They are 
all wearing uniforms with green trousers, brown shirts, and red 
hats and scarfs. They are also carrying weapons of various 
calibers, and they have modern radio communications equipment." 
  He added, "Most of them are Indians, but there are also some 
white people with light-colored eyes." 
  According to this witness, the rebellion began at 0230 (0830 
GMT) when the rebels took over the Justice Palace, which they 
burned. Later, they took over the San Cristobal de las Casas 
Mayor's Office. According to Radio Red, the rebels are also 
causing "disturbances" in other areas of Chiapas State, which 
borders Guatemala. 
  According to reporters, security forces in Chiapas have 
tried 
to persuade the rebels to resolve their problems through legal 
means, but this report has not been officially confirmed. 

</TEXT>

