<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Free San Cristobal Inmates </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0201223394 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2152 GMT 2 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0201223394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tuxtla Gutierrez, Mexico, 2 Jan (EFE) -- Members of 
the Zapata National Liberation Army (EZLN) today freed some 120 
inmates from the prison of San Cristobal de las Casas in 
Chiberos, where the rebels have clashed with military forces. 
  The San Cristobal prison has practically become the line of 
combat between an as of yet undetermined number of EZLN members 
and the forces of the Mexican Army, anonymous sources told EFE. 
  Most of the freed inmates are reportedly Indians, according 
to the sources. The EZLN is made up primarily of Indians of the 
Tzeltales, Tzotziles, and Tojolabales tribes. 
  The sources also reported that the town of Ocosingo 
northwest 
of San Cristobal has been virtually cut off after EZLN members 
blew up the bridges of La Florida and La Virgen at the entrance 
and exit of Ocosingo. 
  It was also reported that the San Cristobal de las Casas Red 
Cross ordered the suspension of its services given the lack of 
guarantees for its workers. 
  At least 14 guerrillas have died and some six soldiers and 
three civilians were injured, two of whom are Red Cross members 
who were injured when the ambulance in which they were traveling 
was fired upon. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

