<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Occupy Guatemalan Border Towns </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0301004294 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0000 GMT 3 Jan 93 </F>
<F P=103> PA0301004294 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tuxtla Gutierrez (Mexico), 2 Jan (EFE) -- News 
sources have confirmed to EFE that the Mexican Army is fighting 
Zapata National Liberation Army [EZLN] rebels in Ocosingo, 
Chiapas State. According to the sources, the rebels occupied the 
towns of Oxchuc, Huixtan, and Guadalupe Tepeyac along the 
Guatemalan border today. 
  According to reports published by EL TIEMPO newspaper of San 
Cristobal de las Casas, Chiapas State, fighting began in 
Ocosingo at about 1500 local time (2100 GMT). There are no 
reports of dead or wounded. 
  The Army has intermittently bombarded the town of Ocosingo 
and there are reports of at least seven separate clashes between 
Army troops and rebel forces resulting in 14 dead and more than 
20 wounded. 

</TEXT>

