<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Secretariat Bulletin No. 1 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0301054994 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 3 Jan 93 </F>

<F P=103> PA0301054994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Bullentin No. 1 issued by the Defense Secretariat in Mexico </F>
City on 2 January; from an XEW "Special Report" -- read by 
announcer] 
  [Text] In light of the events of 30 December 1993 in the 
town of San Miguel, followed by the events that took place in 
the predawn hours of 1 January 1994 in which groups of outlaws 
occupied Ocosingo, Altamirano, Las Margaritas, and San Cristobal 
de las Casas in Chiapas State, all military personnel assigned 
to the 7th Military Region were ordered to remain in their 
barracks. They were to await the results of possible talks led 
by the state government directed at getting the members of the 
offensive armed groups to return to lawfulness. At 0700 [1300 
GMT] today, after leaving San Cristobal, unidentified troops 
surrounded and attacked the military camp housing the 
headquarters of the 31st Military Zone located approximately 10 
km southeast of the aforementioned town. At 1330 [1930 GMT] the 
attacks by said armed groups against the military camp continue. 
The Federal Attorney General delegate was summoned and ordered 
to file a report on the events as soon as possible. 

</TEXT>

