<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armed Clash Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0301013694 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0109 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0301013694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 2 Jan (NOTIMEX) -- The Mexican Army 
reported this Sunday that an unspecified armed group attacked a 
military garrison near the southeastern city of San Cristobal de 
las Casas after armed Indians occupied that town on Saturday. 
  The group sieged and assaulted the garrison of the 31st 
Military Zone, 10 km north of San Cristobal de las Casas, 
Chiapas, and according to the National Defense Secretariat, the 
attack lasted into the afternoon. 
  In the predawn hours of Saturday, armed Indians of the 
self-styled Zapata National Liberation Army (EZLN), which was 
previously unknown, forcefully seized the towns of San Cristobal 
de las Casas, Ocosingo, Las Margaritas, and Altamirano in that 
region. 
  Official reports indicated that the Indians had left San 
Cristobal de las Casas early on Sunday without clashing with the 
Mexican Army. 
  The occupation of the four towns left a toll of three dead 
and some 14 injured. The Army communique did not report 
casualties on the attack against the military zone. 
  The same communique reported that the Army expected "a 
possible dialogue" with the local government of Chiapas -- a 
Mexican state bordering Guatemala -- to see that the "attacking 
groups" cease their illegal actions and resort only to lawful 
means. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

