<H3> <TI>   Terrorist Attack Leaves Two Injured in Lima </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA3112205393 Paris AFP in Spanish 1931 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> PA3112205393 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Lima, 31 Dec (AFP) -- The police reported today 
that at least two persons were injured this Friday, when a rebel 
commando detonated an explosive device at a substation of the 
Peruvian Telephone Company in the Santa Anita District of Lima. 
  According to preliminary reports, an armed group arrived at 
the substation in a vehicle and exploded the device when the two 
guards were sleeping. It was also reported that the explosion 
caused heavy damage to the office and to adjacent buildings. 
[passage omitted] 

