<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports Through 30 Dec </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0101221894 </F>
<F P=103> PY0101221894 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Paraguay monitored through 30 
December. 
  On 29 December Inter-American Development Bank President 
Enrique Iglesias signed in Asuncion a $18.6-million loan to 
finance a package of projects that will benefit municipalities 
and departmental governments. (Asuncion NOTICIAS in Spanish 30 
Dec 93 p 17) 
  The first "electrointensive" metalworking company of 
Paraguay 
run by Brazilians will begin operations in January with an 
initial investment of $50 million. The plant belongs to the 
Brazilian group Ioschpe and is located in Limpio, near Asuncion. 
It has the capacity to produce 60,000 metric tons per year. 
(Sao Paulo GAZETA MERCANTIL in Portuguese 14 Dec 93 p 11) 

</TEXT>

