<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Acting Defense Minister on Presence of U.S. Soldiers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA3012190693 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1730 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> PA3012190693 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] General Ramon Emilio Gil Bermudez, acting defense 
minister, confronted today the dust storm unleashed by the 
arrival of U.S. soldiers in Bahia de Malaga. He insisted that 
it is just a technical collaboration and said that the Armed 
Forces' 1994 objective is to capture the guerrillas' leaders. 
  Gil reiterated today that the presence of U.S. soldiers in 
the Colombian Pacific area is simply due to technical 
collaboration. 
  [Begin Gil recording] The real reason why they--not Marines, 
but military engineers or a detachment of military 
engineers--are here is to execute an operation of mutual 
assistance. [end recording] 
  Gil downplayed the importance of the Americas Watch reports, 
which accuse the mobile brigades of violating human rights in 
certain areas of Colombia. 
  [Begin Gil recording] The reports that reach these 
organizations have already been distorted; they have an 
intention that favors criminals. [end recording] 
  Gil said the Army's main objective for 1994 is to reduce the 
offensive capability of guerrillas and, if possible, capture the 
leaders. 

</TEXT>

