<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rebels Close Off 3 Towns; Declare War on Army </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0101185894 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1806 GMT 1 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0101185894 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 1 Jan (EFE) -- Rebels from the 
self-styled Zapata Liberation Army [Ejercito Zapatista de 
Liberacion -- EZL] have taken over the mayoral offices in the 
towns of Ocosingo, San Cristobal de las Casas, and Las 
Margaritas, where the rebels have set fires and destroyed the 
files of the Attorney General's Offices in these three towns. 
  According to a Mexican television station, the rebel group 
issued a communique this morning. In the communique, the group 
proclaims itself a guerrilla movement and declares war on the 
Mexican Army, which it challenges to fight in the mountainous 
area of the southern state of Chiapas. So far, there are no 
reports of any casualties, but the rebels have closed off the 
entries and exits of those three towns. 

</TEXT>

