<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujimori Orders Reinforced Security </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0101215194 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2034 GMT 31 Dec 
93 </F>

<F P=103> PA0101215194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Lima, 31 Dec (NOTIMEX) -- Peruvian President 
Alberto Fujimori today called on the Armed Forces to redouble 
security measures in Lima and other major cities to prevent more 
terrorist attacks like those that have taken place in past days. 
  During a meeting held this afternoon with the National 
Intelligence Service (SIN) high command, the president gave 
several guidelines to the official forces to encourage them to 
continue struggling effectively against the subversive groups. 
  Fujimori demanded more protection for the population, 
particularly now when the nation is preparing to celebrate the 
new year. 
  Fujimori later traveled to the southern Andean city of 
Arequipa, where he will celebrate the year's end. There he 
evaluated the country's political violence along with the 
intelligence services chiefs and the military high command. 
  Armed Forces and police authorities increased security 
measures in the capital city after several attacks this week 
resulted in two deaths, dozens of injured, and considerable 
property damage. [passages omitted] 

</TEXT>

