<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vietnamese Congratulate Castro on Anniversary </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL3112163593 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> FL3112163593 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Over the last few days, 1 January 1959 has become a 
constant subject in Vietnam, where numerous ceremonies and 
congratulations for the 35th anniversary of the triumph of the 
Cuban Revolution are being reported by Hanoi's media. Du Muoi, 
secretary general of the Vietnam Communist Party, Vietnam's 
President Le Duc Anh, and Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet sent a 
letter of congratulations to Commander in Chief Fidel Castro on 
the occasion of such a highly significant date. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-50536 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat002_a_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-002 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 January 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Provincial Plenum Letter of Commitment to Castro </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL3112143493 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 
GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> FL3112143493 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The people of Pinar del Rio Province have sent 
Commander in Chief Fidel Castro a message reaffirming their 
commitment to further the development of the Revolution and the 
preservation of the accomplishments of socialism. The letter was 
read by Fidel Ramos, first secretary of the Communist Party of 
Cuba [PCC] in Pinar del Rio, during the plenum of the provincial 
PCC Central Committee. 
  This occasion, in addition to being a forum for analysis of 
the province's 1993 performance, was the right moment to read 
the message sent to the province by Army General Raul Castro. 
Raul congratulated the people of Pinar del Rio for their work 
and dedication during the 35th anniversary year of the triumph 
of the Revolution. 

</TEXT>

