<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chile Considers Diplomatic Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL3012190993 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> FL3012190993 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Chilean Foreign Ministry has announced that it 
is ready to advise the government on an eventual decision to 
reestablish diplomatic ties with Cuba. Chilean Foreign Minister 
Enrique Silva Simma explained that no deadline has been set for 
a final decision but affirmed that all aspects of relations with 
Cuba are being analyzed. The Chilean minister added that the 
pace at which his ministry is working complies with the opinion 
expressed by President-Elect Eduardo Frei Ruiz-Tagle to the 
effect that this type of matter must be undertaken slowly. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

