<H3> <TI>   Guatemala Institutes `Strict' Border Security </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0301200094 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1927 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0301200094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1927 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Carlos Arce] </F>
  [Text] We have a last minute report that the Guatemalan 
Armed Forces has implemented strict security measures along the 
border with Mexico. 
  Guatemalan Armed Forces Spokesperson Edith Vargas indicated 
that a military contingent was mobilized to the common border to 
prevent the flow of weapons. Likewise, she deplored the events 
initiated by an armed group in the Mexican state of Chiapas. 
  Meanwhile, Chiapas official spokespersons revealed that the 
Mexican Armed Forces practically have the situation in La 
Margaritas and Ocosingo under control. However, the situation 
is still confusing in Altamirano. In addition, official sources 
have refused to confirm or deny reports that Governor Absalon 
Castellanos has been kidnapped. 

</TEXT>

