<F P=103> PA0401194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] In order to facilitate the pardoning of soldiers 
who participated in the 4 February and 27 November coup 
attempts, President Ramon J. Velasquez urged them to abide by 
the law so that decisions in that regard can be made within the 
legal framework. 
  President Velasquez is studying the possibility of issuing a 
new list of soldiers to be pardoned, including officers who 
sought asylum in Peru. He invited them to return to the 
country, guaranteeing their safety. He stressed that Venezuela 
is ruled by laws based on the Constitution, which is a guarantee 
for all Venezuelans. 

