<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Comments on Mexican Events </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0401154594 Guatemala City Teleonce Television in Spanish 
0400 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0401154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Teleonce Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Telepress" newscast] </F>
  [Text] So far, the Mexican Government has not sent the 
Guatemalan Government any official notification on the 
disturbances taking place in southern Mexico, Guatemalan Foreign 
Minister Arturo Fajardo Maldonado has announced. 
  The foreign minister ruled out that the events taking place 
in the neighboring country will affect the role Mexico is 
playing as host for the Guatemalan peace process at a time when 
the first dialogue of 1994 is about to begin this week. 
  [Begin recording] [Fajardo Maldonado] These are strictly 
internal affairs of Mexico [words indistinct]. 
  [Unidentified reporter] Will you consult with the Guatemalan 
Embassy in Mexico about this situation? 
  [Fajardo Maldonado] No, I have not consulted the embassy. 
This is a Mexican issue [words indistinct]. 
  [Reporter] Don't you think this situation might affect the 
peace talks that will begin very soon [words indistinct]? 
  [Fajardo Maldonado] I have no information to that effect, so 
therefore, [words indistinct]. [end recording] 

